eurocash.firstPart: We apply this Privacy and Cookie Policy (the Policy) when you visit the Eurocash1 website. This Policy does not apply when you browse other companies' websites by accessing the Eurocash1 website.
eurocash.secondPart: We collect data on visitors to our website in accordance with the Law on the Legal Protection of Personal Data of the Republic of Lithuania, the Law on Electronic Communications of the Republic of Lithuania, the Law on the Protection of Personal Data of the European Union, other relevant legal acts and instructions of controlling authorities.
eurocash.thirdPart: We use cookies to collect data about your use of the website. The types of cookies and their purpose are listed in the table below.
eurocash.fourthPart: We responsibly protect the data we collect about visitors to the Eurocash1 website from loss, unauthorized use and alteration. Eurocash1 employees have a written commitment not to disclose or disseminate information about the company's customers, including visitors to the Eurocash1 website, to third parties.
eurocash.fifthPart: When you visit the Eurocash1 website, we want to provide information and features tailored just for you. This requires cookies. These are small pieces of information stored in your web browser. They help us to identify you as a previous visitor to the Eurocash1 website, save the history of your visit to the website and adapt the content accordingly. Cookies also help to ensure the smooth operation of the website, allow you to monitor the duration and frequency of visits to the Eurocash1 website and collect statistics on the number of visitors to the website. By analyzing this data, we can improve the site and make it more convenient for you. You can choose to use cookies by visiting the Eurocash1 website. If you do not agree to the storage of cookies on your computer or other device, you can revoke your consent to use them at any time by changing the settings and deleting the stored cookies.
